React is a open-source library that was created by Meta (Facebook). The main purpose of creating this is to build fast and interactive web and mobile applications. In HTML we create the whole page as a single massive file. But in react we can create small reusable pieces called components as a user interface. The advantage of this is code reusability, the code can be written once and run anywhere and it’s easy to maintain also. Because of this React is very popular among web developers now. In this small blog I am going talk about how I started to learn react as a complete beginner.
