Setting Up React
Node.js is not needed for user to run web application in his browser. We need it to develop react applications. The reason is the browser cannot natively read react languages like JSX. Because of that we use node.js to maintain extremal resources and code packages.
Create a React App
npm create vite@latestAfter run this you will see lots of files and dependencies those are the things that need to run and develop React applications on our browser.
When talking about React we must talk about JSX which means JavaScript XML. This is used to tell the interface how it should look like using JavaScript. The flex of this is we can use HTML like markup directly in JavaScript file. Then it will convert into JavaScript and show in browser.
Components in React
Components are reusable small pieces of code. This is same as JavaScript function. The difference is this piece of code output HTML. There are two types of components in React.

• Class components

• Function components
Below is a example of creating a component and how to use it. These components are reusable and easy to maintain.
function Navbar() {
return <h1>Navbar</h1>;
}<Navbar />
Props — Properties
In react components we can pass arguments as props. Which means properties. This argument will pass to the component as a HTML attribute.
React State
React state is data that can change over time, and when its changes react automatically updates the UI. As a example a switch with a light has two states On and OFF. When switch is on light will automatically work. And when it’s off light changes automatically. In code when state change it naturally updates the UI.
